Project - Cardio Good Fitness

Objective:¶

This project is to study the Customers data of the treadmill product(s) of a retail store - Cardio Good Fitness.

Cardio Good Fitness is a retail store that sells treadmill product(s). It has collected Customer data for each of their users across the various prodcuts. This project is to:

  • Study the Customer profile (characteristics of a customer) of the different products
  • Perform univariate and multivariate analyses
  • Generate a set of insights and recommendations that will help the company in targeting new customers.

Following are the attributes of the Dataset collected for the analysis:

  • Product - The model no. of the treadmill
  • Age - Age of the customer in no of years
  • Gender - Gender of the customer
  • Education - Education of the customer in no. of years
  • Marital Status - Marital status of the customer
  • Usage - Avg. # times the customer wants to use the treadmill every week
  • Fitness - Self rated fitness score of the customer (5 - very fit, 1 - very unfit)
  • Income - Income of the customer
  • Miles- Miles that a customer expects to run

# Creating a function to display the values of the attributes against the chart
def displayValues(feature):
    ax = sns.countplot(data=df, x=feature); 

    plt.rcParams["figure.figsize"] = [7.00, 3.50]
    plt.rcParams["figure.autolayout"] = True
    
    for p in ax.patches:
       ax.annotate('{:.1f}'.format(p.get_height()), (p.get_x()+0.25, p.get_height()+0.5))

    plt.show()

# Creating a common function to draw a Boxplot & a Histogram for each of the analysis
def histogram_boxplot(data, feature, figsize=(12, 7), kde=True, bins=None):
    f2, (ax_box2, ax_hist2) = plt.subplots(
        nrows=2,  # Number of rows of the subplot grid= 2
        sharex=True,  # x-axis will be shared among all subplots
        gridspec_kw={"height_ratios": (0.25, 0.75)},
        figsize=figsize)  # creating the 2 subplots
    
    sns.boxplot(data=data, x=feature, ax=ax_box2, showmeans=True, color="violet")  # boxplot will be created and a star will indicate the mean value of the column
    
    if bins:
      sns.histplot(data=data, x=feature, kde=kde, ax=ax_hist2, bins=bins, palette="winter")
    else: 
      sns.histplot(data=data, x=feature, kde=kde, ax=ax_hist2)  # For histogram
    
    ax_hist2.axvline(data[feature].mean(), color="green", linestyle="--")  # Add mean to the histogram
    
    ax_hist2.axvline(data[feature].median(), color="black", linestyle="-")  # Add median to the histogram

Observations:

  • Income has a high positive correlation with Education & Age
  • Miles run has high positive correlation with Usage & Fitness
  • Age has a lower correlation with Fitness, Usage and Miles
  • Fitness has higher correlation with Usage
  • Education has a postive correlation with Fitness & Usage

Conclusion:¶

  • There are 3 unique product models for which the sample data was collected
  • TM195 is the largest sellling product and liked by Customers of all ages. It can be priced economically that fits the budget of all type of users
  • Most of the users maintain a fitness level of 3 when they use treadmill on an average of 3 times/week
  • Customers with more years of education seem to be using treadmills more and maintain their fitness at high levels
  • Age does not seem to be a barrier for fitness and as long as usage and increase in miles run, the fitness level is good
  • Based on the high fitness level of the TM798, it can be marketed for customers who are fitness experts
  • TM798 treadmill can be priced higher considering the Fitness advantage and its liked by more educated & high income users
  • TM498 can be focused towards Female users since they seem to like this product more and have high level of usage
